result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:31 pm - DA calls cases 16CF39 and 16CM59 and states appearances and agreement reached.  Defendant Vladimir J. Zirngibl appeared with attorney James Richard Lex.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Judge Madden is handling 16CM59 on general assignment.  DA files information on felony, acknowleged and reading is waived. DA asks that Ct 1 in the information be amended to 943.20(3)(bf), a class I felony.  So ordered.  Lex has filed a waiver of preliminary hearing on this.  Court questions DE and accepts waiver.  DE enters plea of NO CONTEST to amended Count 1 on 16CF39.  Court questions DE regarding the plea.  Victims are allowed to speak.  DE responds.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  DE to submit DNA sample at PRSO.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty of Ct 1 on 16CF39 and orders entry of JOC.  On motion of DA, dismisses Ct 2 and dismisses but reads in 16CM59.

Court imposes:
Sentence withheld - 3 years probation
Conditions of probation
60 days jail, 30 days initial confinement, and 30 days held open for probation agents discretion.  60 days to report to jail.
$600 fine which includes $250 DNAAS
$555.28 restitution plus $55.53 surcharge for a total of $610.81
DE must submit an apology to victim/victims in way and manner to be determined by probation agent.
Submit to AODA assessment within 30 days and comply with any recommendations.  
Defendant may petition the court for expungment if probation is successfully completed

DE is advised to rights as a felon.

Appeal rights given.
Plea/sentencing hearing on January 10, 2017 at 11:00 am.

If not already completed DE must submit to booking at Sheriff's Dept prior to release.
Defendant shall give written notice prior to any change in address or telephone number to the Clerk of this Court and Defense Attorney.  Defendant may not have contact with Douglas Leitl and Michelle Boness, unless written consent is filed with the Clerk's office or outside business hours with the Price County Sheriff's Dept.

16CM59 and 16CF39.  Defendant Vladimir J. Zirngibl appeared with attorney James Richard Lex.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint acknowledged, reading waived.  Time limits waived on felony.  Plea not guilty on misd. One bond for both.
